Description: Way to Calvary. Among the various compositions of this subject to which Bruegel's is very close, is also the one by Cornelis Massys at Brussels (other version, signed formerly Zátka Coll. Budweis), with the group of the Virgin & St. John isolated in foreground on the right. The connection between the Brussels Cornelis Massys & Bruegel also noticed by G.M. in Cat. of exh. Le siècle de Bruegel 1963, p. 123, N° 103 and by E. de CALLATAY, Cornelis Massys paysagiste...[= Cornelis Massys paysagiste, collaborateur de son père et de son frère et auteur de l'Album Errera], Bull.Mus.R. des B.-A. de Belgique, XIV, 1965, [pp. 49-70] p. 69-.
